            . I am a <rs id="t18240916-248-viclabel1325" type="occupation">stationer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240916-248-victim2074 t18240916-248-viclabel1325"></join>, and live in Red-lion-street, Holborn; I missed nine copper plates on the 8th of September; the prisoner had been at work for me, but was not then; I made enquiries, and heard the prisoner had pledged some things with Mr. Brown, at the corner of Neville-court. I went there and found two of the plates; I suppose them worth about half a crown a piece; I have seen six others since; he had frequently been in my house; they were kept in the work room at the top of the house, he worked in that room.</p>
